 Arsenal drub Charlton 3-0

 - Premier League 

 London: Rejuvenated Arsenal cranked up the pressure in the battle for the fourth Champions League spot with a stylish 3-0 win at home to Charlton Athletic in the Premier League on Saturday. 

Robert Pires, Emmanuel Adebayor and Alexander Hleb struck as Arsenal registered a third consecutive league win to go fourth in the table, one point above north London rivals Tottenham Hotspur. 

Louis Saha scored twice for second-placed Manchester United in a 2-1 victory at West Bromwich Albion that cut Chelseas lead to 12 points. On Sunday, Chelsea play at Fulham and third-placed Liverpool travel to Newcastle United. 

Blackburn Rovers, Bolton Wanderers and Wigan Athletic maintained their challenges for a Champions League berth. Rovers beat Middlesbrough 3-2 despite having Robbie Savage sent off while Bolton overpowered bottom club Sunderland 2-0 and Wigan won 1-0 at Manchester City. 

The title race may be a foregone conclusion but the scrap for fourth spot is coming to the boil, with Arsenal running into form at the right time. 

Despite a lengthy injury list they completely outclassed London rivals Charlton, Pires applying the finishing touch to a flowing move after 13 minutes and Adebayor doubling the lead before halftime. (Reuters) 




